About 180 golfers are expected to feature in the Ibadan Golf Club (IGC) Captain’s Inaugural tournament, planned to usher in Tunji Oladosu as the new captain of the club scheduled for June 24 to 25. The Chairman of the inaugural committee, Idowu Salami , said during a press briefing organized ahead of the event in Ibadan that the tournament would also witness big social interactions between cream de la cream in the society that are expected at the event.   Salah crowned PFA Player of the Year     African Athletics Championships: Amusan strikes gold in…     Nigeria beats Brazil at Kwibuka Cricket Tourney   He said: “The inaugural tournament is always organized to celebrate and usher in the Captain of the Ibadan Golf Club. When a new captain comes on board, it is in our tradition to celebrate him. And golfers all over the country are expected to grace the occasion. “The arrival, registration, and cocktail is on Friday, June 24 while the tournament will snowball into the closing ceremony and presentation of prizes on Saturday. The tournament will be an epoch-making event and players from Ikeja Golf Club, Ikoyi Golf Club, IBB Golf Club, Ibom Golf Club, Ekiti Club, and a host of others”. Speaking in the same vein, Wale Osungbohun, the second vice Captain of IGC stated that the tournament will be full of fanfare, stating that the Ibadan golf club is known to be among the leading golf clubs in Nigeria. Other members of the tournament committee include Otunba Abimbola Davis